Load dataset

diagon_alley_data <- read.delim("ep1_dataset_diagon_alley_shops.txt")


# shuffling data
rows <- sample(nrow(diagon_alley_data))

# reordering data
diagon_alley_data <- diagon_alley_data[rows, ]
head(diagon_alley_data)
# show clean table using kableExtra
kbl(diagon_alley_data[1:10,], caption = "Diagon Alley Shops") %>%
  kable_styling(bootstrap_options = c("striped", "hover"))

Explanation of dataset
  • shops The shops in Diagon Alley
  • price_per_item_type_in_galleons Price per item type in Gold Galleons. For example, dress robe is an item type and each shop sells multiple types of items.
  • number_of_items_in_inventory For each item type, this variable represents the number of items in stock.
  • total_revenue_per_item_type_in_galleons Revenue for each item type per year in Gold Galleons.

Creating a basic plot of revenue versus distance from the Diagon Alley entrance

p <- ggplot(data = diagon_alley_data) + 
  geom_point(mapping = aes(x = price_per_item_type_in_galleons, y = total_revenue_per_item_type_in_galleons))

p

Changing x and y axis labels and plot theme

p <- ggplot(data = diagon_alley_data) + 
  geom_point(mapping = aes(x = price_per_item_type_in_galleons, y = total_revenue_per_item_type_in_galleons)) + 
  theme_bw() +
  ylab("Total revenue per item (Gold Galleons)") +
  xlab("Price per item (Gold Galleons)")
p

Aesthetic mappings

Adding colors to shops and specifying color palette using ggsci.

p <- ggplot(data = diagon_alley_data) + 
  geom_point(mapping = aes(x = price_per_item_type_in_galleons, y = total_revenue_per_item_type_in_galleons, color = shops)) + 
  theme_bw() + scale_color_futurama() +
  ylab("Total revenue per item (Gold Galleons)") +
  xlab("Price per item (Gold Galleons)")
  
p

Adding the size aesthetics to scale the points according to the number of item types sold in each shop

p <- ggplot(data = diagon_alley_data) + 
  geom_point(mapping = aes(x = price_per_item_type_in_galleons, y = total_revenue_per_item_type_in_galleons, color = shops, size = number_of_items_in_inventory)) + 
  theme_bw() + scale_color_futurama(alpha=0.5) +
  ylab("Total revenue per item (Gold Galleons)") +
  xlab("Price per item (Gold Galleons)")

p

Facets

Splitting plots into facets, which are subplots, one for each shop

p <- ggplot(data = diagon_alley_data) + 
  geom_point(mapping = aes(x = price_per_item_type_in_galleons, y = total_revenue_per_item_type_in_galleons, color = shops, size = number_of_items_in_inventory)) + 
  theme_bw() + scale_color_futurama(alpha=0.5) +
  facet_wrap(~ shops, nrow=2) +
  ylab("Total revenue per item (Gold Galleons)") +
  xlab("Price per item (Gold Galleons)")
  
p
